text: Here's a stream of consciousness for what I did...in case it makes sense to someone out there (not me): Noticed that the LI29 BPM 401 was offline, so I tried to reconfigure the LI28 feedback to not use BPM 401. I added BPM LI29 201 to the feedback instead. Feedback had error BPM TMIT too low for LI29 BPM 401, which didn't make any sense. Decided to try to reboot the IOC for LI29 BPM 401 and it came back (we'll have to monitor it to see for how long). Then I reconfigured the feedback again and removed LI29 BPM 201. Had an error about the TMIT for BPM LI29 201 being too low, which didn't make any sense. I re-added BPM LI29 201 to the feedback and got error "Failed to compute F matrix". I ran the matrices and the error went away and the feedback is running normally. TLDR; I guess try running the matrices after reconfiguring the feedback and that may wake it up?
